Bruce Reed has been announced as the new Chief of Staff for the Office of the Vice President, succeeding Ron Klain. Reed previously worked as the Executive Director of the Bowles-Simpson Commission. Vice President Biden expressed his admiration for Reed, stating that they have worked closely together in the past. Additionally, Michael C. Donilon, one of Biden's closest advisors, will be returning to his previous position as Counselor to the Vice President. Reed's previous experience includes working as the Chief Domestic Policy Advisor to President Clinton and playing a role in the passage of landmark welfare reform and education agendas. Reed's formal title will be Assistant to the President and Chief of Staff to the Vice President.